\f0 \cf0 \uc0\u55356 \u56812 \u55356 \u56807 
\f1  Today is the anniversary of the death of 
\f2\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Paul Erd\uc0\u337 s
\f1\b0  (1913-1996), the famous {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hungarian_mathematician"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Hungarian mathematician}}. He was one of the most prolific {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematician"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 mathematicians}} and producers of mathematical {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conjecture"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 conjectures}} of the 20th century. He was known both for his social practice of mathematics (he engaged more than 500 collaborators) and for his eccentric lifestyle. He devoted his waking hours to mathematics, even into his later years\'97indeed, his death came only hours after he solved a geometry problem at a conference in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warsaw"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Warsaw}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Erd\uc0\u337 s pursued and proposed problems in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Discrete_mathematics"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 discrete mathematics}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graph_theory"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 graph theory}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Number_theory"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 number theory}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_analysis"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 mathematical analysis}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Approximation_theory"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 approximation theory}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Set_theory"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 set theory}}, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Probability_theory"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 probability theory}}. Much of his work centered around {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Discrete_mathematics"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 discrete mathematics}}, cracking many previously unsolved problems in the field. He championed and contributed to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ramsey_theory"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Ramsey theory}}, which studies the conditions in which order necessarily appears. Overall, his work leaned towards solving previously open problems, rather than developing or exploring new areas of mathematics.\cb1 \
\cb3 Erd\uc0\u337 s published around 1,500 mathematical papers during his lifetime, a figure that remains unsurpassed. He firmly believed mathematics to be a social activity, living an itinerant lifestyle with the sole purpose of writing mathematical papers with other mathematicians. Erd\u337 s's prolific output with co-authors prompted the creation of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erd%C5%91s_number"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Erd\uc0\u337 s number}}, the number of steps in the shortest path between a mathematician and Erd\uc0\u337 s in terms of co-authorships.\
\

\f0 \uc0\u55356 \u56814 \u55356 \u56825 
\f1  \'c8 oggi l\'92anniversario della morte di Paul Erd\'f6s (1913-1996), il famosissimo matematico ungherese. \'c8 stato uno dei matematici pi\'f9 prolifici ed eccentrici della storia. Ha lavorato e risolto problemi legati alla {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teoria_dei_grafi"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 teoria dei grafi}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Combinatoria"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 combinatoria}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teoria_dei_numeri"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 teoria dei numeri}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analisi_matematica"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 analisi}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teoria_dell%27approssimazione"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 teoria dell'approssimazione}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teoria_degli_insiemi"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 teoria degli insiemi}} e {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Probabilit%C3%A0"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 probabilit\'e0}}. In generale, si \'e8 sempre concentrato sul risolvere problemi non risolti gi\'e0 esistenti piuttosto che creare nuovi rami di ricerca. Ha dato, d\'92altro canto, il suo nome ad un innumerevoli congetture matematiche. \
Al giorno della sua morte, Erd\'f6s \'e8 il matematico con pi\'f9 pubblicazioni della storia: pi\'f9 di 1500, un numero che fa impallidire i pi\'f9 e che rimane ad oggi insuperato. \
Credeva che la matematica fosse un lavoro \'93sociale\'94 e per questo intratteneva e creava collaborazioni con amici e colleghi matematici in continuazione promuovendo uno stile di vita itinerante con il solo obiettivo di creare articoli scientifici.\
